quran[86]{c,v,t}:
  78,1,About what are they asking one another
  78,2,About the momentous news
  78,3,the thing about which they differ
  78,4,No indeed! They will soon know
  78,5,"Again, no indeed! They will soon know"
  78,6,Have We not made the earth a flat carpet
  78,7,and the mountains its pegs
  78,8,We have created you in pairs
  78,9,We made your sleep a break
  78,10,We made the night a cloak
  78,11,We made the day for earning a living
  78,12,We built seven firm layers above you
  78,13,We installed a blazing lamp
  78,14,We sent down cascading water from the clouds
  78,15,so that by it We might bring forth grains and plants
  78,16,and luxuriant gardens
  78,17,The Day of Decision is a fixed appointment
  78,18,the Day the Trumpet is blown and you come in droves
  78,19,and heaven is opened and becomes doorways
  78,20,and the mountains are shifted and become a mirage
  78,21,Hell lies in wait —
  78,22,a homecoming for the profligate
  78,23,remaining in it for countless aeons
  78,24,not tasting any coolness there or any drink
  78,25,except for boiling water and scalding pus —
  78,26,a fitting recompense
  78,27,They did not expect to have a reckoning
  78,28,and utterly denied Our Signs
  78,29,We have recorded all things in writing
  78,30,So taste! We will increase you only in punishment
  78,31,For those who have taqwa there is triumph
  78,32,Gardens and grape vines
  78,33,and nubile maidens of similar age
  78,34,and an overflowing cup
  78,35,where they will hear no prattle and no denial
  78,36,"a recompense from your Lord, a commensurate gift"
  78,37,"Lord of the heavens and earth and everything between them, the All-Merciful. They will not have the power to speak to Him"
  78,38,"On the Day when the Spirit and the angels stand in ranks, no one will speak, except for him who is authorised by the All-Merciful and says what is right"
  78,39,That will be the True Day. So whoever wills should take the way back to his Lord
  78,40,"We have warned you of an imminent punishment on the Day when a man will see what he has done, and the kafir will say, ´Oh, if only I were dust!´"
  79,1,By those who pluck out harshly
  79,2,and those who draw out gently
  79,3,and those who glide serenely
  79,4,and those who outrun easily
  79,5,and those who direct affairs
  79,6,On the Day the first blast shudders
  79,7,and the second blast follows it
  79,8,hearts that Day will be pounding
  79,9,and eyes will be cast down
  79,10,"They will say, ´Are we to be restored to how we were"
  79,11,"when we have become perished, worm-eaten bones?´"
  79,12,"They say, ´That will clearly be a losing restoration!´"
  79,13,There will be but one Great Blast
  79,14,"and at once they will be on the surface, wide awake"
  79,15,Has the story of Musa reached you
  79,16,when his Lord called out to him in the holy valley of Tuwa
  79,17,´Go to Pharaoh — he has overstepped the limits —
  79,18,"and say: \"Do you resolve to purify yourself"
  79,19,"I will guide you to your Lord so that you may fear Him?\"´"
  79,20,Then he showed him the Great Sign
  79,21,But he denied it and disobeyed
  79,22,and then he hastily backed away
  79,23,But then he rallied and called out
  79,24,"saying, ´I am your Lord Most High!´"
  79,25,So Allah made an example of him seizing him with punishment in the next World and this world
  79,26,There is certainly instruction in that for those who fear
  79,27,Are you stronger in structure or is heaven? He built it
  79,28,He raised its vault high and made it level
  79,29,He darkened its night and brought forth its morning light
  79,30,After that He smoothed out the earth
  79,31,and brought forth from it its water and its pastureland
  79,32,and made the mountains firm
  79,33,for you and for your livestock to enjoy
  79,34,When the Great Calamity comes
  79,35,that Day man will remember what he has striven for
  79,36,and the Blazing Fire will be displayed for all who can see
  79,37,As for him who overstepped the bounds
  79,38,and preferred the life of this world
  79,39,the Blazing Fire will be his refuge
  79,40,But as for him who feared the Station of his Lord and forbade the lower self its appetites
  79,41,the Garden will be his refuge
  79,42,"They ask you about the Hour: ´When will it come?´"
  79,43,What are you doing mentioning it
  79,44,Its coming is your Lord´s affair
  79,45,You are only the warner of those who fear it
  79,46,"On the Day they see it, it will be as if they had only lingered for the evening or the morning of a single day"